LORE umbral
FLAGS UMBRAL
Shadow given permanent form; bodies are partially anti-light-constituted;
the eye slides off them slightly in any light — a passive characteristic
Daylight appearance: lean, pale-gray, very dark eyes (pupil/iris often
indistinguishable), charcoal-to-void-black hair, faintly iridescent skin;
in shadow: outlines soften; in darkness: extremely difficult to see
Origin: long-term habitation in the Gloamvault beneath Midgaard, where the
Black Sun Shard's anti-light leaks into the world; the change is heritable
The Gloamvault predates Midgaard's First Stone Accord; Umbral communities
maintained and guarded it before the city existed above it
The Kel'Shadra Order established formal operations in the Vault by claiming
an existing site shaped by centuries of Shard influence
Not demons, not undead, not evil; a different relationship to existence;
capabilities inaccessible to fully material beings
~
